-- Indian shares mark 1-week closing high; blue-chips gain
-- By Abhishek Vishnoi
-- Tue May 06, 2014 06:06AM EDT
-- None



MUMBAI, May 6 (Reuters) - Indian shares rose for a second consecutive session on Tuesday to mark their highest close in a week as blue-chips such as Reliance Industries gained after foreign investors snapped a five-day selling streak in index futures.

Reliance Industries <RELI.NS> provisionally rose 1.9 percent while ICICI Bank <ICBK.NS> ended 2.1 percent higher.